text: First of all the Ouija board has only existed since 1890...that's hardly "centuries" as mentioned in the trailer.  Second, the planchette is the "centuries old" device, so really it is the piece that you move that holds the "power" so to speak and not the board.  Planchettes were used originally for auto writing and it wasn't until Elijah Bond wanted a patent on planchettes that he came up with the idea for the Ouija board and it wasn't used for divination until WWI. It's amazing what two minutes of research can turn up.

If you're one of those hardcore skeptics, I have a challenge for you: 1: Get an Ouija board (not one from wal-Mart or whatever but preferably, an old, vintage, possibly-but-most-likely-not-haunted one off of eBay or any site you can find one). 2. Research any guidelines on how to use the board. 3. Grab some friends, candles, and a video camera/smartphone or two (more cameras=more angles) 4. Find a creepy cemetery, abandoned church, or some creepy woods. 5. Draw a huge pentacle (a pentagram inside a circle) on the ground and light a candle on each point (while this is mostly to create a ritualistic atmosphere, it could possibly heighten the experience). 6. Sit inside the pentacle with your friends and the board. The cameras should be set up. 7. Start the Ouija board session; for maximum results, try to provoke evil spirits 8. One finished, upload footage to YouTube. *If anyone actually does this and nothing bad happens, I might reward a cash prize, but probably not, since I just got laid off the other day. lol*

Unrested souls want to be heard, so when you attempt to talk to them just for fun, they take it as an opportunity to haunt and follow you no matter what, since you now know that they exist. Ignorance is a bliss. Believe me, I'm an angel of the Lord. lol¬†
author: Castiel Angel

text: Hollywood has to sugar coat everything. Sure, the Ouija board isn't going to give results as the movie depicts, but it's real. It's rather amusing to read the comments of people arguing about it. It's only natural for somebody who hasn't had an experience to say "It's not real". And, for the record, it has NOTHING to do with Christianity, or any other "Modern" monotheistic religion, or belief. Many cultures have "Occult" beliefs, and are still very much active in their "Religious" practices. A Ouija board won't bring in anything that isn't already there. If you don't believe, you don't believe. There's no need to act like a douche, just to prove a point, or kill time, or feed your ego, or whatever your excuse is. It's real. If you want proof, go prove it. I, as have many many other people, have seen, and heard, and felt my experiences. I know the spirit world is real. ¬†

text: If Casper the friendly ghost appears, he is more than welcome to stay. All the other ones can go right back where they came from! I mean, "normal" life is hard enough as it is, without those "frighteners" keeping us up all night. We've got jobs and school to go to the next morning. None of this hanky-panky and creeping about in my or anyone else's house at this ungodly hour. But if they insist on being hard of hearing, I will sue him, her or it for "disturbing of domestic peace", and in case of more things going "bump¬† in the night", I shall play "Get A Life" by GoreFest ever so loudly. And then who will be sorry...? But all joking aside for a moment. When it comes to things we don't understand or can't explain, the best thing to do is to keep an open mind. Because until this very day, NOBODY has come up with the ultimate answer (or indeed the solution) to this "strange" and sometimes frightening phenomena we tend to call "the occult". Or is this just a simpleton's opinion? But when you take famous cases from the past, like for instance "The Entity" (a woman being haunted and repeatedly raped by an invisible being over many years), "The Amityville Horror" (a family being terrorized by "something evil" in a house where years ago a family was murdered) or even the "paranormal" activities that went on in "Poltergeist"; did some of that "scary stuff" really happen, or was it all made up? Personally, I'm not saying yes. But I'm not saying no either. Because, as they say: "there's more between heaven and earth". And I wasn't there, when those people saw, hear, felt, or smelled anything out of "the ordinary". And although I like a good horrorfilm from time to time (because it usually deals with the things we really don't want to talk about, like death and our own mortality) the Greatest Thing a human being on this "funny"", "little" planet can posses is ofcourse...L O V E... And I like to think, probably THE most powerful force in any dimension or universe. So, if one day some "evil spirit" likes to play "silly buggers" with a person who has L O V E¬† in abundance in his or her life. Then he or she should confront "the unknown" by saying in a loud and steady voice: "I've got L O V E to protect me..." "So bring it on!" In short: If you do good in this world (without behaving like a total goody two shoes!) no real harm will come to you. Even if I'm fully aware that the most horrendous and tragic things happen to the nicest people among us. So, what does all of that teach us? That life isn't fair, and we all have to suffer at one time or another. But in the meantime, we try to do our utmost best to become a decent member of society, (again, without being a total goody two shoes!), love the people we love, and in the end leave our beloved earth behind with some sort of achievement. But before that "Greatest Mystery" finally pays us a visit, we're stuck (but hopefully enjoy) with movies that gives us a shiver or two. Culminating in the one sentence that will remind you of checking under your bed before you go to sleep and dream of happy thoughts:    ¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† "It knows what scares you"      P.S.:¬† But L O V E¬† and¬† H U M O U R will always prevail in the end...

text: Paranormal and supernatural beliefs associated with Ouija have been harshly criticized by the scientific community. The action of the board can be parsimoniously explained by unconscious movements of those controlling the pointer, a psychophysiological phenomenon known as the ideomotor effect.¬†As in reflexive responses to pain, the body sometimes reacts reflexively to ideas alone without the person consciously deciding to take action. For instance, tears are produced by the body unconsciously in reaction to powerful emotions. The effects of automatic writing, dowsing, facilitated communication, and Ouija boards have been attributed to the phenomenon. Mystics have often attributed these effects to paranormal or supernatural force. Many subjects are unconvinced that their actions are originating solely from within themselves.

text: HORRIBLE! - First off this is basically a modern age remake of Witchboard (1986). For a new story it had so much potential but lacked in so many ways. I'm really biting my tongue on giving away the movie, but why does every new paranormal horror film director feel the need to keep using the actress Lin Shaye? Anyways the special effects where atrocious, typical cheap paranormal CGI poo. The film is too quiet almost no music. And when the characters die you hear silence then little "splats." Some of the characters die off in ways that are never shown. Some become possessed and some don't. The ending makes no since whatsoever. I kept waiting for a shocking surprise or secret that reveals the power of the board or planchete which audiences have never seen...and surprise surprise same stuff that's been done before. Several scenes in the trailer wasn't even in the movie. I watched the movie with four other friends and everyone looked at each other and said, "sooo that's it? what a waist." I would honestly save your money if you plan on seeing this in theaters.

text: This is real, don't take my word for it but do it your self if you're a skeptic, is all I can honestly say to any none believers. I wouldn't do it again, if I were too get paid??? totally but just for the heck of it nah. I did this with a couple of my friends when I was in the 7th grade, a couple of hours before Halloween, we stayed up all night playing the xbox and roasting each other then decided to do it . When we did it like the first 4 times nothing actually happened, but on the fifth attempt the room got cold and everybody thought it was the air cutting on, but we felt the vents and the heat was actually blowing. At this point we're still thinking it's a game not a big deal. So the sixth time we read from the paper and put all of our hands on the Ouija and I remember getting a little headache and I was looking around and I saw little blue and purple sparkles, like the ones you get when you get hit in the head or after a good workout. I thought I was the only person feeling and seeing this, so I looked at my friend Gera and he said I see little sparkling lights flying around the room and everybody else did too, the moment we all tried to take our hands off the little clip thingy it felt like we could move easily with no problem but we couldn't for like at least 5sec before actually letting go. We were all laughing and joking about it but I swear everybody felt a little sick like drained of energy, it wasn't even 10mins later that we all just went to sleep because we randomly got tired as hell. If anybody doesn't believe that they aren't real and is 100% fake I would advise you to try it your self. ¬†

text: It‚Äôs not the spiritual pressure moving your hand, it‚Äôs a subconscious part of your brain which moves your hand subconsciously.   You‚Äôre spelling out random words, even creepy words and sentences/phrases.   Basically the creepy writings coming from ouija board does NOT come from spiritual pressure or spirits, even demons. It‚Äôs coming from your own brain.  Here‚Äôs another slight explanation towards it:   You know when the light-bulb has gone in your room but even so when you enter your room you subconsciously flick the light switch? ¬†The psychological effect that happens, the same with ouijas.  Or when you walk into a room forgetting what you went for? The same effect.  Maybe you wont know the true corruption of your mind until you use an ouija board. You‚Äôll understand how idiosyncratic your brain works and how disturbing you truly can be.  And I‚Äôm stating that, when using ouija board, feeling possessed, or frightened? That‚Äôs more or less the placebo effect of having not known the psychology behind ouijas beforehand.  Ouija boards are a game, and it's the psycholgy that's creepier.

text: People of the internet. The paranormal effects of Ouija boards are none existent, because you allow yourself to truly believe it is this is why you experience what you believe to be a paranormal event.  The human mind is very powerful and very open to suggestion of information, so much so that it can change your perception of reality and trick your senses.  When I was young I used to suffer from Night terrors, Waking Night terrors, Hallucinations of both sound and image and sleep paralysis.  This was because I had an over active and very strong suggestive imagination. My brain did not know how to process the difference between what was real and what was not whilst experiencing this. As a child I believed in spirits and demons as most children do. As I grew in age I could see more clearly with my knowledge I was able to use reason and logic to determine the cause of my problems.  I stopped believing in spirits and demons and almost overnight the Hallucinations stopped haunting me.  I still every now and then get sleep paralysis and the odd waking night terror hallucinations. But I know they're not real and they can't hurt me.

text: I've been explorin' the paranormal world as a side job, on and off for the past 9 years, and I've done the unimaginable to provoke evil spirits or any spirits for all I care... and ofcourse part of my research was the Ouija Board. I've used the Ouija Board in a haunted hospital, haunted old castle, haunted school and also inside a cemetery- right in between the graves at midnight. I must've used the Ouija Board more than 100 times, with different people, different places, under different circumstances and also by myself... and nothin' ever happened. My moral of the story is; the Ouija Board is bullshit and so are all the ghost stories your grandmother tells you. All the stuff I've experienced and recorded (from slammin' doors to breakin' glass and strange noises) in haunted areas and buildings could be scientifically explained. Actually you don't even need science, you only need half a brain. From my opinion as an experienced veteran of this shit; spirits may exist but only in their own world. They cannot touch us, harm us or possess us... we cannot see them, feel them or hear them. ANYONE WHO TELLS YOU SOMETHIN' ELSE IS FULL OF SHIT!¬†My conclusion is; 50% of people believe in ghosts based on stories they've heard from others and blindly believed, 20% make up stories for attention and believe their own stories, 20% genuinely believe in ghosts but they also believe in the toothfairy and Santa... and the last 10% are retarded.

We heard millions of voices and screaming too, the sound of dead people. We ran to the front door and onto the street were we saw the black figure go into the house, we waited outside till about 3am the next day, 2 of my cousins fell asleep in the gutter while me and my other cousin entered the house to see what was happening. Zozo (the ouija board devil) was gone but the electricity was still out. We decided to put the board back into the attic/man hole and I was smaller than my cousin so I had to climb in there. My cousin was waiting down the ladder while I army crawled to the shelf when I felt something behind me, I looked behind Me and nothing was there. I rolled to my side to look around when I heard something else crawling my way. I switched the lighter on and there was a dead Asian man with half a body (he only had from his head to his waist line) army crawling towards me. I screamed and my cousin dragged me out of there by the feet. We ran back outside to find that 1 of the cousins was missing while the other one was lying on the floor with blood n bruises all over her. The cousin that was with me was fine so was I. Till this day my cousin is still missing and the other one was put in a mental institution. My other cousin and I believe that Zozo took her with him into The Other Side.
author: TeshBear W
